Fix module wildcard tap pattern matching

DESCRIPTION:
Tap pattern `input:* -> *` (match all events in input module) does not
match any events. No tap calls are inserted into the AST.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
1. Tap pattern `input:*` correctly matches all events in input module
2. Logger tap fires for hello() and goodbye() calls
3. Test passes with output: "[TAP] input:hello\nHello\n[TAP] input:goodbye\nGoodbye\n"

ROOT CAUSE:
Likely issue in taps.kz pathMatches() function (around line 114) or
in the module qualifier handling. The pattern "input:*" should:
1. Extract module="input" and path="*"
2. Match invocations where module_qualifier="input" (or fallback_module="input")
3. Match path="*" (wildcard)

RELATED:
- See also: 510_070 (metatype binding), 510_072 (event wildcard patterns)
